-- Whole-model verification summary
----------------------------------------------------------------------

-- Summary 1: Model defines operations for adding/viewing blood units with permissions and access control.
-- Summary 2: Includes acceptance criteria reachability predicates and test scenario contracts.
-- Summary 3: Edge case assertions check for missing data, expired units, and duplicate IDs.
-- Assumption 1: BloodUnit extends Resource to represent tracked units.
-- Assumption 2: hasCompleteData and isExpired fields model ABO/Rh type and collection date completeness.
-- Assumption 3: Pre1 and PostDone states represent before and after operation states.
-- Open issue 1: Availability NFR (nfr_fact_availability_redundancy) requires at least 2 channels per operation, but only one API interface exists, making it unsatisfiable.
-- Open issue 2: Performance NFR (nfr_fact_performance_latency) limits channels to <=2 and targets to <=3, which may conflict with availability requirement.
-- Open issue 3: Edge case assertions (ec_safe_1, ec_safe_2) forbid any operation involving incomplete or expired blood units, which may be too strict for real-world scenarios.


